<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-08-01T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-08-01T07:00:00-05:00" n="171" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d171">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">862.5151/1727: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Berlin</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Jenkins</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-08-01T13:00:00+01:00">August 1, 1936—1
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received August 1—9:35 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Foreign exchange control order issued today provides “payments from Aski
                            accounts for the deliveries of goods to the United States <pb facs="0347" n="248" xml:id="pg_248"/> may not be made after August
                            3, 1936, except deliveries based on contracts closed prior to August 3,
                            1936. Permits for private barter transactions with the United States
                            shall not be issued after August 3, 1936.”</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Jenkins</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>